author: akarasulu
msg: Inserted result error code prefixes into some of the NamingExceptions
thrown and also made code conform to coding standards.

author: akarasulu
msg: Added some more documentation about the nature of the parser.  Also note
that in the last revision the MultiMap parse() overload is deprecated as
we make the transition towards the Attributes based architecture for
representing entries both in the server and within clients.

author: akarasulu
msg: The LDIF parser now populates all attributes including control attributes
like 'dn' and 'changeType' as specified by RFC 2849 which can be found here
http://www.faqs.org/rfcs/rfc2849.html.  Based on the context of use the
control attributes may need to be removed from the Attributes or MultiMap
instance populated by the parser.  Both the 'dn' and the 'changeType'
properties need to be removed where client implementations are concerned.

msg: Added the binaryflag column to the MySQL configuration example,
